name: 4D Nucleome
description: Study of the three-dimensional organization of the nucleus in space and time (the 4th dimension)

name: Genotype-Tissue Expression
description: An ongoing effort to build a comprehensive public resource to study tissue-specific gene expression and regulation

name: The Human Microbiome Project
description: Characterization of healthy and disease-associated human microbiomes using multiple 'omics technologies

name: The Gabriella Miller Kids First Pediatric Research Program
description: A large-scale data resource to help researchers uncover new insights into the biology of childhood cancer and structural birth defects

name: Library of Integrated Network-Based Cellular Signatures
description: A library that catalogs changes that occur when different types of cells are exposed to a variety of agents that disrupt normal cellular functions

name: Metabolomics
description: Studies of chemical reactions that occur in organisms, cells, or tissues (metabolomics) to inform basic, translational, and clinical research

name: Molecular Transducers of Physical Activity in Humans
description: A catalogue of biomolecules affected by human exercise, biomolecular changes resulting from movement, and relationships between these changes and benefits to human health
